§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We generalize convex functions to arbitrary vector spaces. ⦉
⦉

§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Suppose $(X, 𝗥)$ is a real vector space. ⦉

  ‖ Then $f: X → 𝗥$ is ❬convex❭ if
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ f(tx + (1-t)y) ≤ tf(x) + (1-t)f(y) ⦉
    ⦉
    for all $t ∈ [0,1]$ and $x,y ∈ X$. ⦉
⦉

§ Example ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Any norm is a convex function. ⦉
⦉

